The paper deals with deep convolutional neural network (CNN) inference, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. The use of low precision fixed-point numbers is also a common technique in hardware design (cs.AR) and optimization (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the efficiency of different weight representations, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
